# 🚀 COMPLETE BUSINESS WORKFLOWS - Step by Step Guide
#
# 📚 This file contains complete end-to-end business scenarios
# Each workflow is self-contained and demonstrates real-world usage
#
# 🎯 HOW TO USE:
# 1. Execute each step in sequence (1a, 1b, 1c, etc.)
# 2. Copy values from responses where indicated
# 3. Observe how stock levels change throughout the process
# 4. Each workflow is independent - you can run them in any order

# 🏷️ VARIABLES
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@apiVersion = /api/v1

###############################################################################
# 🛍️ WORKFLOW A: SUCCESSFUL E-COMMERCE ORDER
# Complete customer journey from browsing to purchase
###############################################################################

### A1. Customer browses product page - Check availability
# Product: Laptop HP Pavilion 15
# Customer sees: "X units available" on product page
GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/inventory/stock/2d70d1dc-cd3a-4f40-afb0-52e16445bf36
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: workflow-a-browse

### A2. Customer adds to cart and proceeds to checkout
# System reserves stock to prevent overselling during checkout
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/inventory/reserve
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: workflow-a-checkout

{
  "product_id": "2d70d1dc-cd3a-4f40-afb0-52e16445bf36",
  "quantity": 1,
  "request_id": "checkout-{{$timestamp}}-laptop",
  "timeout_seconds": 600,
  "reason": "Customer checkout process",
  "client_id": "ecommerce-web",
  "metadata": {
    "order_id": "ORD-{{$timestamp}}",
    "customer_id": "customer-{{$randomInt 1000 9999}}",
    "product_name": "Laptop HP Pavilion 15",
    "unit_price": "899.99",
    "checkout_step": "payment_processing"
  }
}

### A3. Verify stock is now reserved (available should decrease, reserved increase)
GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/inventory/stock/2d70d1dc-cd3a-4f40-afb0-52e16445bf36
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: workflow-a-verify

### A4. Payment successful - Complete the order
# 📝 COPY THE RESERVATION_ID from step A2 response
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/inventory/release
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: workflow-a-complete

{
  "reservation_id": "PASTE_RESERVATION_ID_FROM_A2",
  "reason": "purchased",
  "request_id": "complete-{{$timestamp}}"
}

### A5. Final check - Stock permanently reduced, ready for shipping
GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/inventory/stock/2d70d1dc-cd3a-4f40-afb0-52e16445bf36
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: workflow-a-final

###############################################################################
# 🛒 WORKFLOW B: ABANDONED SHOPPING CART
# Customer abandons cart, stock is automatically released
###############################################################################

### B1. Customer adds expensive item to cart
# Product: Sony WH-1000XM4 Headphones ($349.99)
GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/inventory/stock/47569eb2-fe19-43cb-929d-aedfd59dc199
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: workflow-b-initial

### B2. Item reserved during cart session (15 min timeout)
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/inventory/reserve
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: workflow-b-cart

{
  "product_id": "47569eb2-fe19-43cb-929d-aedfd59dc199",
  "quantity": 1,
  "request_id": "cart-{{$timestamp}}-headphones",
  "timeout_seconds": 900,
  "reason": "Shopping cart hold",
  "client_id": "mobile-app",
  "metadata": {
    "cart_id": "cart-{{$randomInt 10000 99999}}",
    "session_id": "session-{{$guid}}",
    "platform": "iOS",
    "product_name": "Sony WH-1000XM4",
    "unit_price": "349.99"
  }
}

### B3. Customer hesitates, checks competitors (stock still reserved)
GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/inventory/stock/47569eb2-fe19-43cb-929d-aedfd59dc199
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: workflow-b-hesitate

### B4. Customer decides not to buy - Abandons cart
# 📝 COPY THE RESERVATION_ID from step B2 response
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/inventory/release
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: workflow-b-abandon

{
  "reservation_id": "PASTE_RESERVATION_ID_FROM_B2",
  "reason": "cancelled",
  "request_id": "abandon-{{$timestamp}}"
}

### B5. Stock returned to available pool for other customers
GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/inventory/stock/47569eb2-fe19-43cb-929d-aedfd59dc199
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: workflow-b-released

###############################################################################
# 📦 WORKFLOW C: WAREHOUSE OPERATIONS
# Complete supply chain from receiving inventory to first sale
###############################################################################

### C1. Check current SSD inventory before shipment
GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/inventory/stock/f7d85ff3-6dbf-4ee8-bd61-54453610e441
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: workflow-c-before

### C2. Warehouse receives new SSD shipment
PUT {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/inventory/stock
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: workflow-c-receive

{
  "product_id": "f7d85ff3-6dbf-4ee8-bd61-54453610e441",
  "new_stock": 25,
  "adjustment_type": "restock",
  "reason": "Received Samsung SSD shipment",
  "reference": "PO-{{$timestamp}}",
  "request_id": "receive-{{$timestamp}}",
  "metadata": {
    "supplier": "Samsung Electronics",
    "shipment_id": "SHIP-{{$randomInt 100000 999999}}",
    "received_by": "warehouse_team",
    "units_received": 25,
    "unit_cost": "89.99",
    "batch_code": "SSD-{{$timestamp}}"
  }
}

### C3. Inventory updated - Verify new stock levels
GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/inventory/stock/f7d85ff3-6dbf-4ee8-bd61-54453610e441
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: workflow-c-updated

### C4. First customer orders from new inventory
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/inventory/reserve
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: workflow-c-order

{
  "product_id": "f7d85ff3-6dbf-4ee8-bd61-54453610e441",
  "quantity": 2,
  "request_id": "order-{{$timestamp}}-ssd",
  "timeout_seconds": 300,
  "reason": "Customer order - fresh inventory",
  "client_id": "web-store",
  "metadata": {
    "order_id": "ORD-{{$timestamp}}",
    "customer_id": "customer-{{$randomInt 5000 9999}}",
    "unit_price": "129.99",
    "promotion": "new_stock_discount"
  }
}

### C5. Order processed immediately (fast fulfillment)
# 📝 COPY THE RESERVATION_ID from step C4 response
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/inventory/release
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: workflow-c-fulfill

{
  "reservation_id": "PASTE_RESERVATION_ID_FROM_C4",
  "reason": "purchased",
  "request_id": "fulfill-{{$timestamp}}"
}

### C6. Final inventory after first sale from new shipment
GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/inventory/stock/f7d85ff3-6dbf-4ee8-bd61-54453610e441
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: workflow-c-final

###############################################################################
# �� WORKFLOW D: CORPORATE BULK ORDER
# B2B customer orders complete office setup
###############################################################################

### D1. Corporate customer plans office setup - Check bulk availability

# Check monitor availability (need 3 for new team)
GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/inventory/stock/fc39adf6-784c-43f3-bb0d-9ed79613dd21
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: workflow-d-check-monitor

# Check keyboard availability
GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/inventory/stock/e08e3e7e-9126-49e4-9caf-63885a07bd78
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: workflow-d-check-keyboard

# Check mouse availability
GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/inventory/stock/2da3b8d3-69f1-46e6-a068-874532d5126a
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: workflow-d-check-mouse

### D2. Atomic bulk reservation - All items must be available
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/inventory/batch/reserve
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: workflow-d-bulk

{
  "requests": [
    {
      "product_id": "fc39adf6-784c-43f3-bb0d-9ed79613dd21",
      "quantity": 3,
      "request_id": "bulk-{{$timestamp}}-monitors",
      "timeout_seconds": 3600,
      "reason": "Corporate setup - Dell monitors",
      "client_id": "b2b-portal",
      "metadata": {
        "corporate_id": "CORP-{{$randomInt 1000 9999}}",
        "company": "TechStartup Inc",
        "department": "Engineering",
        "setup_type": "new_team_workstations"
      }
    },
    {
      "product_id": "e08e3e7e-9126-49e4-9caf-63885a07bd78",
      "quantity": 3,
      "request_id": "bulk-{{$timestamp}}-keyboards",
      "timeout_seconds": 3600,
      "reason": "Corporate setup - Keychron keyboards",
      "client_id": "b2b-portal",
      "metadata": {
        "corporate_id": "CORP-{{$randomInt 1000 9999}}",
        "company": "TechStartup Inc",
        "department": "Engineering",
        "setup_type": "new_team_workstations"
      }
    },
    {
      "product_id": "2da3b8d3-69f1-46e6-a068-874532d5126a",
      "quantity": 3,
      "request_id": "bulk-{{$timestamp}}-mice",
      "timeout_seconds": 3600,
      "reason": "Corporate setup - Logitech mice",
      "client_id": "b2b-portal",
      "metadata": {
        "corporate_id": "CORP-{{$randomInt 1000 9999}}",
        "company": "TechStartup Inc",
        "department": "Engineering",
        "setup_type": "new_team_workstations"
      }
    }
  ]
}

### D3. Verify bulk reservation succeeded
GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/inventory/stock/fc39adf6-784c-43f3-bb0d-9ed79613dd21
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: workflow-d-verify-monitors

GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/inventory/stock/e08e3e7e-9126-49e4-9caf-63885a07bd78
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: workflow-d-verify-keyboards

### D4. Corporate payment approved - Complete first item (example)
# 📝 COPY ONE RESERVATION_ID from step D2 batch response
# In real system, all would be completed programmatically
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/inventory/release
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: workflow-d-complete

{
  "reservation_id": "PASTE_RESERVATION_ID_FROM_D2_BATCH",
  "reason": "purchased",
  "request_id": "corp-complete-{{$timestamp}}"
}

###############################################################################
# 🔧 WORKFLOW E: INVENTORY MANAGEMENT
# Admin operations for stock corrections and adjustments
###############################################################################

### E1. Inventory audit finds discrepancy
GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/inventory/stock/834004f0-f683-4e96-ae6b-bb6673869d24
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: workflow-e-audit

### E2. Physical count shows more inventory than system
PUT {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/inventory/stock
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: workflow-e-correction

{
  "product_id": "834004f0-f683-4e96-ae6b-bb6673869d24",
  "new_stock": 15,
  "adjustment_type": "correction",
  "reason": "Physical inventory count correction",
  "reference": "AUDIT-{{$timestamp}}",
  "request_id": "audit-{{$timestamp}}",
  "metadata": {
    "auditor": "inventory_team",
    "audit_date": "2025-10-06",
    "system_count": "195",
    "physical_count": "210",
    "difference": "+15",
    "audit_id": "AUD-{{$randomInt 1000 9999}}"
  }
}

### E3. Customer returns defective RAM
PUT {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/inventory/stock
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: workflow-e-return

{
  "product_id": "834004f0-f683-4e96-ae6b-bb6673869d24",
  "new_stock": 2,
  "adjustment_type": "return",
  "reason": "Customer return - defective units replaced",
  "reference": "RET-{{$timestamp}}",
  "request_id": "return-{{$timestamp}}",
  "metadata": {
    "return_reason": "defective",
    "customer_id": "customer-{{$randomInt 1000 9999}}",
    "return_date": "2025-10-06",
    "condition": "defective",
    "action": "refund_issued",
    "rma_number": "RMA-{{$randomInt 10000 99999}}"
  }
}

### E4. Final inventory after adjustments
GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiVersion}}/inventory/stock/834004f0-f683-4e96-ae6b-bb6673869d24
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: workflow-e-final

###############################################################################
# 📊 MONITORING & TESTING UTILITIES
###############################################################################

### Health Check - Always start here
GET {{baseUrl}}/health
Content-Type: application/json

### API Documentation - Open in browser
GET {{baseUrl}}/docs

### OpenAPI Specification - For API tools
GET {{baseUrl}}/openapi.json

###############################################################################
# 📝 WORKFLOW SUMMARY
#
# A. E-commerce Success: Browse → Reserve → Pay → Complete
# B. Cart Abandonment: Add to cart → Reserve → Abandon → Release
# C. Supply Chain: Receive inventory → Update stock → Sell → Fulfill
# D. B2B Bulk Order: Check availability → Batch reserve → Approve → Complete
# E. Inventory Management: Audit → Correct → Handle returns → Update
#
# 🎯 Each workflow demonstrates:
# - Stock visibility and real-time updates
# - Optimistic locking preventing overselling
# - Idempotent operations for reliability
# - Comprehensive audit trail via metadata
# - Business rule enforcement
# - Error handling and recovery
#
# 💡 Tips:
# - Always copy reservation_id from responses
# - Check stock before and after operations
# - Use meaningful metadata for business context
# - Monitor request_id for distributed tracing
###############################################################################
